text: def modify_numbers(arr):     modified_arr = []     for num in arr:         num_str = str(num)         for i in range(len(num_str) - 1):             if num_str[i] > num_str[i + 1]:                 modified_arr.append(int(num_str[:i] + num_str[i + 1] + num_str[i] + num_str[i + 2:]))                 break         else:             modified_arr.append(num)          return modified_arr   # Example usage arr = [5555, 4444, 3333, 2222, 1111] modified_arr = modify_numbers(arr) print(modified_arr)

author: @tejasgosavi7395
text: Awesome video sir keep uploading videos like this my code def convert(n,pre):     for i in range(1000,9999):         count=0         a=int(i)         b=int(n)         for j in range(0,4):             if a%10!=b%10:                 count+=1             a=a//10             b=b//10         if count<=1 and pre<i:             return(i) l=[x for x in input().split()] ans=[] for i in range(len(l)):     if i!=0:         ans.append(convert(l[i],ans[i-1]))     else:         ans.append(convert(l[i],0)) print(ans)
